BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CONFLICT DE-ESCALATION SCRIPTS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.0 Td (When co-parenting gets heated, use these:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 666.2 Td (  * 'Let's focus on what's best for [child's name].') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 652.2 Td (  * 'I hear your concern. Can we find a middle ground?') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 638.2 Td (  * 'Let's table this and discuss when we're both calm.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 624.2 Td (  * 'I'm willing to compromise on ___ if you can on ___.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 610.2 Td (  * 'Can we communicate about this in writing instead?') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 596.2 Td (  * 'I don't agree, but I respect your perspective as their parent.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.2 Td (  * 'Let's ask our mediator/therapist about this one.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 558.4 Td (GOLDEN RULE: Never put the child in the middle. Never badmouth the other parent to the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 544.4 Td (child. Your child loves you BOTH.) Tj ET
